In this paper, we focus on implicit feedback and propose a dual metric learning framework to handle the above issues. As users involve in two heterogeneous graphs, we model the user-item interactions and social relations simultaneously instead of directly incorporating social information into user embeddings. Specifically, as shown in Fig. 1, we propose to model the two kinds of relations as interaction vector (e.g., \documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
